        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 6:02PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 601 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Opal, or 21 miles southwest of Faith, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Faith, Marcus, Howes, Stoneville, Opal, Red Owl, and Durkee Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
